Description:
Light, Bright and Funky
As close to new as it gets without having to endure the process of building yourself, this funky, split level 4 bedroom home offers first home buyers and young families an opportunity to start out with an eye for style. Designed and constructed with clever planning and careful thought, it maximises the advantages of the 617sqm block and is flooded with natural light.
Featuring polished timber floors and stairs, open design and contemporary feel, you will enjoy the space and lifestyle offered. Wow your friends and spread right out on the lower level in the spacious open plan living area which consists of a kitchen just begging to entertain (with its 900mm stainless steel Lofra appliances, dishwasher space and masses of storage), meals area, opening to entertaining deck, and lounge with stunning gas log fire. This area provides both a view and access to the huge deck and spacious sunny garden at the rear of the home, ideal for bbqs and summer evenings with friends. An ideal place for the kids to play with loads of room for them to run, the yard is safe, secure and clearly visible from the home.
The bedrooms are spacious, with the master bedroom featuring a large walk in robe and ensuite with double shower, and the remaining three have ample built in storage and share the upper level with a family bathroom, separate wc and handy linen.
Add to the layout the architectural features, rendered exterior, designer lighting and plush carpets, data network cabling in every room PLUS the location within walking distance of shops, schools and the Bellarine Rail Trail and you have everything you could possibly ask for.
- 617 sqm approx.
- Walk to shops, schools
- 2 years young
- Striking architectural features
- Large double garage
Land: 617 sq m approx.

Description:
Plenty of Room for EVERYTHING!
It is not just the home that is huge, the north facing entertaining deck is quite literally enormous, the double garage has a third bay of workshop space and the land it all sits on is approximately 1096m2 in size,. All this is within walking distance of the town centre and local schools, in a quiet court location opposite the beautiful Drysdale Reserve and sporting facilities.
Just a few years young, the contemporary design of this home offers oodles of space for your family with an open plan design that provides maximum versatility. 4 flowing living areas including lounge, meals, family and rumpus zones, all take advantage of the north sun so they are light, airy and perfect for formal and informal recreation and relaxation. With most new homes nowadays opting for galley style kitchens, the unusually spacious style of this one sits beautifully in the centre of the home and boasts other features such as granite benchtops, 900mm Technika appliances, dual drawer dishwasher, pot drawers galore and a walk in pantry...truly a foodie's delight!
The study at the front of the home would be perfect for home based businesses whilst the master suite next door is the epitome of WOW! With its own private outdoor deck, ensuite with double vanity, separate wc and double shower plus a walk in robe, it is everything you could ever ask for as the ultimate parent's retreat. A further 3 queen sized bedrooms have built in robes with access to a completely functional family bathing area with double vanity, shower/bath room and wc all contained within their own zones to enable multiple simultaneous use.
The top quality specification is evident throughout with polished timber floors, designer lighting in addition to an abundance of mood creating downlighting, extra ceiling height and wet area tiling. The outdoor space is amazing and incorporates both undercover and landscaped open air entertaining area, low maintenance garden beds plus a huge rear yard with garden sheds and plenty of room for summer cricket or football matches for all the family...
- 1096m2 allotment
- Walk to Drysdale Reserve
- Walk to shops and schools
- Huge family home
- Quality finish
Also view standalone web site www.24marshcourt.com
Land: 1096 sq m approx

Description:
ROMANCE AND HISTORY COMBINE TO CREATE BLISS IN THIS UNIQUE HOME.
Rare opporuntiy this 1920's, 1st world war soldiers settlement cottage, has been loved and added to over the years framed by everchanging matured gardens. No. 55 is on approx. 2100sqm of land and has views over the bay. Formal lounge & large sunroom/dining have northern orientation and take advantage of the views, whilst the 3rd living has been added onto the kitchen to provide east light and indulge in the gardens ...the superb window design is a great feature. Three bedrooms with BIR's, two bathrooms, front enclosed verandah & outdoor entertaining area complete the home. Features include central heating, marble fireplace, woodburner, polished floors, big pantry, 3 tanks (70000ltrs) double garage, plus off road for 6 cars maybe more. Short drive to Drysdale with the bustop at the end of the road. SECLUDED with all the amenities on the doorstop.

Description:
Sustainable Lifestyle
Positioned in a quiet, leafy street just a short stroll to the Historic Drysdale Train Station, this contemporary styled home is set on a generous 1866sqm(approx) allotment. The property offers everything you need for sustainable living including large vege patch, a variety of fruit trees, 45,000 litres water storage for garden and house use, a Quantum heat pump(classified as a solar hot water system) to heat your water economically and a 2.1 kilowatt Solar System all ensuring energy efficiency. The architecturally designed home offers 3 bedrooms master with walk through robe to ensuite, and an updated family bathroom, open light filled main living & meals area leading to well equipped kitchen including dishwasher & electric appliances. Backing onto the Bellarine Rail Trail, and located within minutes of walking tracks, Drysdale and it's attractions and amenities. An inspection will not disappoint!
